Tonight marks one year since my album Friendly Fire was released.

This album has become another major turning point in my life. 

Telling my story of faith and queerness through the music has connected me to so many inspiring people around the world who are also out there on the search for something bigger than themselves.

I just want to say a very heartfelt thank-you to everyone who bought, streamed and shared my baby. Thank you for the messages and stories you’ve sent me about how the songs have spoken to you. 

Getting to hear rooms full of strangers sing my music back to me was one of my favourite parts of 2022.

I found out in this last month that I won’t be working with Atlantic Records on the next chapter, so today I’m feeling particularly grateful that I had the experience of making this very special album. 

I’m not done telling the story of these songs and I also can’t wait to show you what comes next. I’ve been relieved to discover there is in fact more to say. Quite a lot really haha.

Let’s just say I’ve never felt better about being in a worse career situation than I am right now hahaha.

Love you all and Happy Birthday Friendly Fire!

Bx

————————————
The gallery of photos are just some of the highlights of the last year:

1. The beautiful album artwork by @a__gilmore 

2. Playing my songs for Atlantic COO Julie Greenwald overlooking Times Square was surreal

3. Watching the album’s story find it’s way out there was scary and exciting

4. My insane album launch party that I got to spend with my best friends like @charlottenicdao 

5. I got to work with my favourite music video director @samuelaaronbennett

6. Speaking at the @grammymuseum with my friend @guskenworthy 

7. Singing on the @kellyclarksonshow with @callmeviane, @andydelossantos, and @astynturr 

8. Meeting @jillianbell and making the funniest music video ever with my heroes @charliedayofficial and @maryelizabethellis (which is in competition at SXSW next week!)

9. Going on tour and seeing cities and faces I’d never seen before. I can’t believe I sold out Joes Pub!

10. Hearing rooms full of strangers sing like choirs of angels

Ugh. I love you all.

Tomorrow I’m going to Austin for #SXSW because the music video that @jillianbell directed for my song ‘If I Didn’t Love You’ is screening in competition!

Making this video was unbelievably fun. And the day went so smoothly it’s hard to believe it was Jillian’s directorial debut. It’s a testament to her genius thet so many amazing people assembled to bring this video to life.

I’m so excited to watch it in a theatre full of people and celebrate her brilliance.

Here are a bunch of BTS clips from the day. Maybe I’ll post more who knows.

Thanks for having us @sxsw !!!!

The music video competition was amazing and seeing @jillianbell’s directing talent on the big screen was bloody awesome.

Given this video was a self-funded venture, it felt really special to see everyone’s hard work celebrated by an audience.

Pictured: 

@kristensreality and @brandondermer, our brilliant producers

@maryelizabethellis, one of our brilliant movie stars (when they first appeared on screen and the audience gasped she turned to me and said “you’re welcome”)

And of course @jillianbell who wrote and directed the whole thing

———-

Obviously now I just want to make more videos. So who wants to kill me next?

I'd love to see you there and if anyone wants to help with merch at any of the shows feel free to drop me a message!

LOS ANGELES!!!! TICKETS ON SALE NOW

You cannot imagine how excited I am to tell you the Ben Abraham Christmas Special™️ is happening in LA for the first time.

I’ve done these for 13 years (someone in the comments will correct me on this) in Melbourne and it’s always my favourite show of the year.

There’s no opener. I do two sets—one set of my own music (cos captive audience lol) and then after a short intermission we play a set of Christmas and holiday themed tunes where I invite some special guests to join. And fam the guest list is already mind blowing.

It’s super relaxed and fun and you’re gonna love it. Just ask any of the Aussies who come every year.

I’ll see you guys on December 4th at the beautiful @elreytheatre 

🎄🤩🎄🤩🎄🤩🎄🤩🎄🤩🎄🤩

‘Never Been Better’ is out now all over the world 🤩🥰

I’m so proud that this is my first independent release in 10 years.

I’m truly in the IDGAF era of my creative process and I’ve never felt more creatively fulfilled.

Thank you for listening and for sharing my music. It’s the only way I get to keep doing what I do.

Written with @brianwbrundage
Produced by Ethan Schneiderman with additional production by @brianwbrundage 
Mixed by @pedrocalloni
Mastered by @beckermastering 

Also I have no budget for a music video so feel free to make all the TikTok, Instagram and YouTube content you like. 

Can’t wait to show you more. Love you lots. Bx
